          <physDesc>
            <p>Paper, about 5 7/8 in. by 4, consisting of 114 leaves, many of
                        which are much soiled and torn, especially foll. <locus from="1">1</locus>, <locus from="9">9</locus>, <locus from="11">11</locus>, <locus from="18">18</locus>, <locus from="36">36</locus>, <locus from="40" to="42">40—42</locus>,
                        <locus from="50">50</locus>, <locus from="51">51</locus>, <locus from="55" to="60">55—60</locus>, <locus from="91" to="97">91—97</locus>, <locus from="100">100</locus>, <locus from="113">113</locus>, and <locus from="114">114</locus>. The quires, signed with letters,
                        are now 12 in number; but leaves are wanting after foll. 8, 10, 97, and 106,
                        as well as at the end. There are from 7 to 11 lines in each page.</p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>
                           <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="114">114 ff.</measure>
                        </extent>
                        <condition>
                           <list>
                              <item>
                                <p>Paper, about 5 7/8 in. by 4, consisting of 114 leaves, many of
                                  which are much soiled and torn, especially foll. <locus from="1">1</locus>, <locus from="9">9</locus>, <locus from="11">11</locus>, <locus from="18">18</locus>, <locus from="36">36</locus>, <locus from="40" to="42">40—42</locus>,
                                  <locus from="50">50</locus>, <locus from="51">51</locus>, <locus from="55" to="60">55—60</locus>, <locus from="91" to="97">91—97</locus>, <locus from="100">100</locus>, <locus from="113">113</locus>, and <locus from="114">114</locus>. The quires, signed with letters,
                                  are now 12 in number; but leaves are wanting after foll. 8, 10, 97, and 106,
                                  as well as at the end. There are from 7 to 11 lines in each page.</p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="2">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="major" script="syr">
                The first eight leaves are written in a neat, regular hand of the
                              <date notBefore="1300" notAfter="1500">xivth or xvth cent.</date>, with many Greek and Syriac
                           vowels.</handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" medium="unknown" scope="minor" script="syr">
                The rest, though of the same date, are very badly written.
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., folio location may not be available for some items below.</note>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <label>Colophon</label>
                  <locus from="105a"/>
                  <p>On fol. 105 a, the scribe has recorded his name,
                    <persName ref="smblPers1182">Domitius</persName>.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܨܠܘ ܥܠ ܕܝܡ̣ܛ ܚܛܝܐ ܘܠܲܠܐ ܘܣܲܟܠܐ ܘܦܲܛܥܐ ܘܓܥ̣ܝܛܐ ܘܓܥ̣ܝܨܐ ܕܣܪܛ܀</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
